block content

  +state(name, path, 'The First State', 'December 7, 1787')

  .intro
    p Delaware was the first state to ratify the U.S. Constitution and displays that date proudly on its flag.
    p A commission group was originally put together for the design, which resulted in the current version, the only one Delaware has flown. Like many other states, the Delaware flag features the state coat of arms, adopted in 1777.
    p The flag was officially adopted July 24, 1913.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Delaware flag features a field of colonial blue surrounding a centered diamond of buff charged with the state coat of arms.
      p “December 7, 1787” (the date Delaware became a state) is inscribed below the diamond in white.
      +survey(name, '52nd')
    .visual.flag
      +flag(name, path)

  .guide.wide
