          h4 water
          p the Delaware River, transportation, commerce
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-delaware-icon-ship.svg', alt='ship with many sails')
          h4 ship
          p shipbuilding, coastal trades

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Coat of Arms
      p The flag features the Delaware coat of arms, adopted in 1777.
      p On the lower banner, the state motto “Liberty and Independence” is inscribed, also heard in the state song, “Our Delaware.”
    .visual.flag
      +coat-of-arms(name, path)

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Colonial blue and buff are Delaware’s state colors.
      p The two colors were inspired by a military uniform George Washington once wore.
      p The Delaware Public Archives provides color values for the #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munsell_color_system') Munsell] and Pantone 1995 color systems.
      hr
      small Values corresponding to imagery:
      small #[strong Colonial Blue]: field <br>
        | #[strong Buff]: diamond, rifleman’s binding, bag, and leggings <br>
        | #[strong Gray Brown]: farmer’s trousers <br>
        | #[strong Brown]: farmer’s hat and hoe, rifleman’s hat and gun stock, ship’s hull <br>
        | #[strong Red Brown]: cow <br>
        | #[strong Red]: farmer’s shirt <br>
        | #[strong Flesh]: face and hands <br>
        | #[strong Orange]: shield’s top panel <br>
        | #[strong Yellow 1]: shield’s frame, branches <br>
        | #[strong Yellow 2]: corn <br>
        | #[strong Yellow 3]: wheat <br>
        | #[strong Green 1]: rifleman’s suit <br>
        | #[strong Green 2]: grass and corn husk <br>
        | #[strong Blue]: shield’s center panel <br>
        | #[strong Blue 2]: emblem below ship <br>
        | #[strong Silver]: emblem below ship<br>
        | #[strong Gray]: rifleman’s flask, feather, and gun barrel <br>
        | #[strong White]: shield’s lower panel
